Ansible doesnâ€™t run natively on Windows, but you can install it using the Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL) or use Cygwin. WSL is preferred for its simplicity.
Install WSL and Ubuntu. Open Ubuntu in WSL and install Ansible as you would on Linux

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install#install-wsl-command

#installing on Lixux
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible

#configuring Ansible Inventory
[webservers]
web1.example.com
web2.example.com

[dbservers]
db1.example.com
db2.example.com

#setting up SSH access
ssh-keygen -t rsa

#generate SSH key
ssh-keygen -t rsa

#coping keys for each server
ssh-copy-id user@remote_host

#configuring the playbooks
---
- name: Install and configure Nginx on web servers
  hosts: webservers
  become: yes
  tasks:
    - name: Install Nginx
      apt: name=nginx update_cache=yes state=present

    - name: Ensure Nginx is running
      service:
        name: nginx
        state: started

#runnig the commands

#running a playbook
ansible-playbook deploy.yml

#checking connectivy to the books
ansible all -m ping


